  'description' => 
  array (
    'en_US' => '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 13pt; color: black; mso-bidi-language: ML;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;"><span style="font-size: 13pt; color: black; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-language: ML; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\';"><strong>Ethical and regulatory challenges in health research <br />University of Hyderabad, Hyderabad <br />December 6-8, 2012<br /><br /></strong></span><span style="font-size: 13pt; color: black; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-language: ML; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\';">The <em>IJME</em> National Bioethics Conference is a platform for different stakeholders to come together and discuss ethical issues in healthcare. The conference provides participants exposure and orientation to bioethics and creates a forum for continued discussion. This year, the theme for the conference is Ethical and regulatory challenges in health research.<br /><span>&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">The <em>Indian Journal of Medical Ethics </em>(<em>IJME</em>) (formerly <em>Medical Ethics </em>and <em>Issues in Medical Ethics</em>), a peer-reviewed, indexed journal, published since 1993, has been a forum for discussion on healthcare ethics for the last two decades. With the evolution of bioethics in India, the need emerged to share ideas, promote original indigenous thinking and research, and develop an ethical framework suitable for the Indian context.&nbsp; The <em>IJME</em> National Bioethics Conferences (NBC) took shape against this background, as a platform for scientific exchanges and debate between different stakeholders in the field. &nbsp;The first NBC was held in Mumbai in 2005, and the second and third NBCs in Bengaluru and Delhi in 2007 and 2010 respectively.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">The 4</span><sup style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">th</sup><span style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"> NBC is to be held in the historic city of Hyderabad, well known for institutes that excel in education and research.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">The 4</span><sup style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">th</sup><span style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"> NBC is intended to bring together the different key constituencies and individuals to share their diverse perspectives on the conference theme &lsquo;</span><strong style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"><em>Ethical and regulatory challenges in health research&rsquo; </em></strong><span style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">with the aim of building a better research enterprise and a favourable environment for of ethical health research. The three-day conference will include five plenary sessions. While the inaugural and closing ceremonies will focus on the broad theme of the conference, the remaining three plenary sessions will focus on specific aspects of health research ethics: (1) interdisciplinary approaches to ethics, (2) clinical trials, and (3) research regulation laws and ethics.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">Parallel sessions will be organised with oral presentations, interactive workshops, symposia and poster sessions.</span><br /> <span style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"><strong>Confirmed plenary speakers include </strong></span><br /> <span style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">Dr T Sundararaman,&nbsp; <strong>&nbsp;</strong>Executive Director, National Health System Resource Centre, and Member and Convener, National Rural Health Mission;</span><br /> <span style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">Professor Ramkrishna Ramaswamy, Vice Chancellor<strong>, </strong>University of Hyderabad;</span><br /> <span style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">Dr G N Rao, Founder and Chairperson, L V Prasad Eye Institute, Hyderabad;</span><br /> <span style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">Dr Prathap Tharyan, Professor and Head, Department of Psychiatry; Christian Medical College, Vellore;</span><br /> <span style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">Dr Vandana Prasad, Member, National Commission for Protection of Child Rights, Government of India, New Delhi, India;</span><br /><span style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"> Dr Veena Shatrugna, &nbsp;Former Deputy Director and Head, Clinical Division, National Institute for Nutrition, Hyderabad;</span><br /> <span style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">Professor Roger Jeffrey, Prof of Sociology of South Asia, and Dean International (India), University of Edinburgh, UK;</span><br /> <span style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">Dr Vasantha Muthuswamy, Former Senior Deputy Director General and Scientist G, ICMR</span><br /> <span style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">Dr Chandra M Gulhati, Monthly Index of Medical Specialties;&nbsp;</span><br /> <span style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">Mr S&nbsp;Srinivasan, LoCost Standard Therapeutics, Vadodara;</span><br /> <span style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">Dr Nandini Kumar, Former Deputy Director General Sr Grade, ICMR;</span><br /> <span style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">Dr Arun Bhatt, Clininvent Research Pvt Ltd, Mumbai.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">We invite you to participate in this conference and contribute to the discussions on this important theme. <strong>&nbsp;</strong></span><br /> <span style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;">Further conference information is available at <a href="../../../../../">http://nbcijme.ijme.in/</a> and with the Conference Secretariat at <a href="mailto:ijme.nbc@gmail.com"> ijme.nbc@gmail.com</a></span></p>
